OL,6,FAt least 80 of Starmer's MPs are
OL,7,Freported to oppose the benefits cuts
OL,8,Fand are said to be furious that a
OL,9,FLabour government is targeting some of
OL,10,Fthe most vulnerable in society.
OL,12,FThe radical package of reforms would
OL,13,Fsee:
OL,15,FThe aim of the measures is to
OL,16,Fmassively increase the incentives for
OL,17,Fpeople to remain in the work-search
OL,18,Fcategory of Universal Credit, even if
OL,19,Fthey suffer with a health condition or
OL,20,Fdisability, but also to more than #6bn
OL,21,Fa year by the end of the decade.
